<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Cistanthe</i> spp. or <i>Gayophytum</i> spp. is characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Achillea</i> <i>millefolium</i>, <i>Achnatherum</i> <i>lemmonii</i>, <i>Achnatherum</i> <i>occidentale</i>, <i>Astragalus</i> <i>bolanderi</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>athrostachya</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>subfusca</i>, <i>Castilleja</i> <i>arachnoidea</i>, <i>Cistanthe</i> <i>monosperma</i>, <i>Cistanthe</i> <i>umbellata</i>, <i>Elymus</i> <i>elymoides</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>spergulinum</i>, <i>Gayophytum</i> <i>diffusum</i>, <i>Gayophytum</i> <i>eriospermum</i>, <i>Gayophytum</i> <i>heterozygum</i>, <i>Gayophytum</i> <i>humile</i>, <i>Gayophytum</i> <i>racemosum</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>brachyantherum</i>, <i>Monardella</i> <i>odoratissima</i>, <i>Navarretia</i> <i>capillaris</i>, <i>Perideridia</i> <i>parishii</i>, <i>Polygonum</i> <i>douglasii</i>, <i>Symphyotrichum</i> <i>spathulatum</i> and <i>Taraxacum</i> <i>officinale</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Abies</i> <i>concolor</i>, <i>Abies</i> <i>magnifica</i> or <i>Pinus</i> <i>contorta</i> ssp. <i>murrayana</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 60 cm; cover is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Astragalus bolanderi</i> > 5% absolute cover with <i>Cistanthe</i> spp. in the herbaceous layer (Potter 1998).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cistanthe</i> and <i>Gayophytum</i> species, or <i>Polygonum douglasii</i> characteristically present; wet meadow indicator species generally absent or in low cover except sometimes <i>Hordeum brachyantherum</i> (Potter 2005).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Dry, raised portions of meadow systems, forest edges. Soils are typically sandy loams.  </div>
</div>

        
